{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771010990,"nonce":"Ni+ID/ATJE9uFnJXfRPsL0JRGyE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qxRPk","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/207","origin":"github"},"title":"feat: add --all-repos flag to pr_status.sh for cross-repo triage","message":"## Problem\n\nThe user browses GitHub across multiple repos to find PRs needing review, PRs with feedback to address, and PRs ready to merge. No single view exists for the entire workspace.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd `--all-repos` flag to `pr_status.sh` to run the existing PR triage logic across all workspace repos (discovered via `list_overlay_repos.py`). Add `make pr-triage` target as a convenience wrapper.\n\n### Changes\n\n- **`pr_status.sh`**: Add `--all-repos` flag\n  - Add `discover_repos()` function reusing `list_overlay_repos.py --include-underlay`\n  - Modify `fetch_prs()`, `get_review_comments()`, `analyze_pr()` to accept optional repo parameter\n  - Modify display functions to show repo name when `.repo` field is present\n  - Update `main()` to iterate repos when `--all-repos` is set\n\n- **`Makefile`**: Add `pr-triage` target running `pr_status.sh --all-repos --simple`\n\n- **`PR_STATUS_README.md`**: Document `--all-repos` flag and `make pr-triage`\n\n- **`CHANGELOG.md`**: Add entry\n\n### Verification\n\n1. `pr_status.sh` (no flags) → unchanged single-repo dashboard\n2. `pr_status.sh --all-repos` → dashboard across all workspace repos\n3. `pr_status.sh --all-repos --simple` → text summary across all repos\n4. `pr_status.sh --all-repos --json` → JSON with repo field\n5. `make pr-triage` → simple text triage output\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}